    "minides": "Ferrari's most powerful production car ever — 1,050 CV from a twin-turbo V8 + three electric motors, 0-100 in 2.25 sec, 330 km/h, 415 kg downforce. The SF90's successor and the Revuelto's nemesis.",
    "description": "Debuted in India on 14 March 2026 at ₹10.37 crore (ex-showroom), the Ferrari 849 Testarossa is the direct successor to the SF90 Stradale and Ferrari's most powerful series-production car ever built. Named after the legendary 1984 Testarossa, it revives the iconic nameplate with a radically modern PHEV architecture. The powertrain pairs a mid-mounted 4.0L twin-turbo V8 (830 CV standalone) with three electric motors — two on the front axle for torque-vectoring AWD and one integrated within the 8-speed DCT — for a combined 1,050 CV and 900 Nm. Performance: 0-100 km/h in 2.25 sec, 0-200 in 6.3 sec, 330 km/h top speed. The 7.45 kWh battery provides up to 25 km of silent EV driving. Active aerodynamics generate 415 kg of downforce at 250 km/h via a twin-tail split rear spoiler. The cabin is driver-focused with a 16-inch digital driver's display (no central touchscreen), a 9-inch passenger screen, physical steering wheel controls (no haptics), and wireless Apple CarPlay/Android Auto integrated into the driver's display. Ferrari's Tailor Made programme offers unlimited personalisation. Deliveries in India begin H2 2026."
  },
